The United Nations has declared June 13, as International Awareness Day for People with Albinism. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Poet and Albinism activist Boitumelo Gaddafi, says people living with the skin condition still face discrimination. Gaddafi says there is a still a long way to go before myths around albinism are completely dispelled. The United Nations has declared the 13 June, International Awareness Day for People with Albinism. READ: Donors urged to give the gift of life Gaddafi says as an activist, he wants to teach people about albinism. “As much as there are people who lack information, my job is to make it easier for people to learn,” Gaddafi said. “I need to liberate, I need to educate and I need to teach about people about albinism.”